Add async version of wrap_tool_call for middleware with checks for passed async function and `await handler`. Tested and verified with my own agent through the following snippet:
```
@awrap_tool_call
async def handle_tool_errors(request, handler):
    try:
        return await handler(request)
    except Exception as e:
        return ToolMessage(
            content=f"Tool error: Please check your input and try again. ({str(e)})",
            tool_call_id=request.tool_call["id"],
            is_error=True
        )
```
